                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden</name>
                    <date when="1886-09-08" rend="right">Sept: 8</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Brother</salute>
                <salute>&#38; Dear Jess</salute>
            </opener> 
            <p>Our hearts out here are with you more than you probably think at this gloomy time.<ptr target="mhs.00023_n1"/> I
                hope &#38; trust you both bear up under it, &#38; that the "God help us" of your
                telegraphic message will be fulfilled&#8212;I find myself better than toward the
                conclusion of former summers&#8212;am still living here at 328 Mickle st&#8212;&#38;
                comfortable.</p><p>&#8212;I am anxious to hear whether Lou got there all right&#8212;am
                sitting here down stairs by the open window as I write&#8212;warm here for two
                days.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="mhs.00023.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
